For those of you in the San Francisco Bay Area who are interested in 
such things, I will be giving a talk at Stanford next Wednesday Oct. 27 
on "Physically-Based Modeling of Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells,", including a 
little about Cantera's capabilities for multiphase heterogeneous 
chemistry / electrochemical simulations. This is part of their Fuel 
Cell Seminar series, and will be held at 4:15 in room 127, building 
530.
